Package: mediawiki-dom-snapshot
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 python3,
 python3-bs4,
 python3-lxml,
 python3-playwright
Recommends: chromium
Description: Headless DOM snapshotter for MediaWiki regression testing
 Drives a headless Chromium against a running MediaWiki instance via
 Playwright, captures the post-JS DOM for a configured set of pages, and
 normalises the output (scrub CSP nonces, ResourceLoader version hashes,
 parser-cache timestamps, lazy-loaded ResourceLoader module styles,
 ...) so the result is diff-stable across runs.
 .
 Use case: detect HTML/CSS changes introduced by MediaWiki core /
 extension upgrades or by site-CSS refactors, by capturing a baseline
 before the change and diffing a fresh capture after.
 .
 Ships with a committed baseline under
 /usr/share/mediawiki-dom-snapshot/baseline/ and the page list under
 /etc/mediawiki-dom-snapshot/pages.conf.
